<br>
Necro w/ EE and Convergence runs to N wall, FDs (make sure necro is bound in oggok).<br>
Mage runs to N wall. If he camps, good, if he doesn't... converge him back in. Necro invites mage to group, mage goes invis (to avoid the patrolling eye), necro gates out.<br>
Necro invites people at portal, while a necro, monk, or SK watches the portal from inside fear.<br>
As portal area is clear, one member of raid at a time zones in and is Call of Heroe'd to the N Wall.<br>
When you hit N Wall, disband and be ready to kill.<br>
<br>
I usually CoH in in this order:<br>
Smartest cleric (NOT highest level)<br>
Smartest enchanter<br>
Biggest, Baddest warrior<br>
Any paladin who can get his boots on the right foot<br>
A Bard over 46th level (feed CoH'er mana)<br>
A Backup Necro (ditto)<br>
then you do: Healer, Melee, Nuker, Healer, Melee, Nuker, etc until the raid is there.<br>
<br>
IF you know how to control aggro, control runners and have a puller with half of a brain, you can even do this when Cazic is at home. <p>Nakath<BR>
The Esoteric Order</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubjond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 362<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/4/02 6:59:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1278.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Bah .. that takes all the fun out of it!</span><hr size=1> Interesting to see how things have changed.  We used to zone in one by one, camp at SW corner, then all log back to kill.  Those that died enroute would have to wait for us to clear the roamers before rez (and first-timers were prohibited from even trying to insert until after roamers were dead).  'Course, that was back in the 50-cap days.  I think we did fear once post-50 with only two groups 55'ish.  Just zoned in and steamrolled over everything.<br>
<br>
BTW, uh, have fear and/or hate been upgraded?  My recollection is that fear was really easy at 55.  And, at about 57'ish, we used to gate up to hate for nice xp and blue diamonds with even a partial group.  I might have the levels a bit wrong, but I'm pretty sure it was in the 55-58 range.<br>
<br>
Back on topic -- I see a veritable army of druids (just kick a tree and 5 or 10 will fall out), fair number of shaman, lots of rangers and paladins, fair rogues, some enchanters and wizards, few mages, almost no warriors. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uxaviarstormburnt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xaviar Stormburnt</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/4/02 7:45:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1278.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bah .. that takes all the fun out of it!</span><hr size=1> We are in great need of good aligned clerics..... our guild has one single cleric.  Many good warriors have died from lack of a cleric.  I am sure to say that if you made a high elf cleric he/she would be adopted by a guild very quickly.<br>
